OL,6,FCivil proceedings were issued at the
OL,7,FHigh Court following reports issued by
OL,8,Fthe now defunct Historical Enquiries
OL,9,FTeam.JThe investigative unit concluded
OL,10,Fit was likely there had been collusion
OL,11,Fbetween individual members of the
OL,12,Fsecurity forces and those responsible
OL,13,Ffor murdering Mr Toland in his
OL,14,Fworkplace at the Happy Landing Bar in
OL,15,FEglinton in November 1976.JIt was also
OL,16,Funable to rule out collusion in Mr
OL,17,FLoughrey's killing at his home in
OL,18,FGreysteel the previous week.JThe
OL,19,Fvictim's widows, Mary Loughrey and
OL,20,FMarie Newton, sued the MoD and PSNI in
OL,21,Fa bid to secure damages.
